  "name": "Venous Thromboembolism - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Labs)",
  "description": "Simulates a hematologist identifying their complete VTE patient population. Real-world identification combines: VTE diagnosis codes, therapeutic anticoagulants, and elevated D-dimer. Tests whether LLM correctly queries multiple FHIR resource types in a multi-query union.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete venous thromboembolism patient population for a quality improvement initiative on anticoagulation duration and bleeding events. From clinical experience, VTE patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal VTE diagnosis (DVT, PE, or extent-specific codes like iliofemoral DVT), most are on therapeutic anticoagulants (warfarin, DOACs like apixaban or rivaroxaban, or enoxaparin), and many had elevated D-dimer at presentation.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any VTE diagnosis (DVT, iliofemoral DVT, IVC thrombosis, PE, or venous embolism)\n2. Patients prescribed therapeutic anticoagulants (warfarin, apixaban, rivaroxaban, dabigatran, or enoxaparin)\n3. Patients with elevated D-dimer (>0.5 mcg/mL FEU)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of VTE dx codes, anticoagulant Rx, and elevated D-dimer Observation. Tests multi-resource union.",
